msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:55 src/languages.md:229
msgid "`name`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:55
msgid "The name of the language"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:56
msgid "`language-id`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:56
msgid ""
"The language-id for language servers, checkout the table at "
"[TextDocumentItem](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/"
"specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#textDocumentItem) for the right id"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:57
msgid "`scope`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:57
msgid ""
"A string like `source.js` that identifies the language. Currently, we strive "
"to match the scope names used by popular TextMate grammars and by the "
"Linguist library. Usually `source.<name>` or `text.<name>` in case of markup "
"languages"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:58
msgid "`injection-regex`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:58
msgid ""
"regex pattern that will be tested against a language name in order to "
"determine whether this language should be used for a potential [language "
"injection](https://tree-sitter.github.io/tree-sitter/3-syntax-highlighting."
"html#language-injection) site."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:59
msgid "`file-types`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:59
msgid ""
"The filetypes of the language, for example `[\"yml\", \"yaml\"]`. See the "
"file-type detection section below."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:60
msgid "`shebangs`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:60
msgid ""
"The interpreters from the shebang line, for example `[\"sh\", \"bash\"]`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:61
msgid "`roots`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:61
msgid ""
"A set of marker files to look for when trying to find the workspace root. "
"For example `Cargo.lock`, `yarn.lock`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:62
msgid "`auto-format`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:62
msgid "Whether to autoformat this language when saving"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:63
msgid "`diagnostic-severity`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:63
msgid ""
"Minimal severity of diagnostic for it to be displayed. (Allowed values: "
"`error`, `warning`, `info`, `hint`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:64
msgid "`comment-tokens`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:64
msgid ""
"The tokens to use as a comment token, either a single token `\"//\"` or an "
"array `[\"//\", \"///\", \"//!\"]` (the first token will be used for "
"commenting). Also configurable as `comment-token` for backwards compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:65
msgid "`block-comment-tokens`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:65
msgid ""
"The start and end tokens for a multiline comment either an array or single "
"table of `{ start = \"/*\", end = \"*/\"}`. The first set of tokens will be "
"used for commenting, any pairs in the array can be uncommented"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:66
msgid "`indent`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:66
msgid ""
"The indent to use. Has sub keys `unit` (the text inserted into the document "
"when indenting; usually set to N spaces or `\"\\t\"` for tabs) and `tab-"
"width` (the number of spaces rendered for a tab)"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:67
msgid "`language-servers`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:67
msgid ""
"The Language Servers used for this language. See below for more information "
"in the section [Configuring Language Servers for a language](#configuring-"
"language-servers-for-a-language)"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:68
msgid "`grammar`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:68
msgid "The tree-sitter grammar to use (defaults to the value of `name`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:69
msgid "`formatter`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:69
msgid ""
"The formatter for the language, it will take precedence over the lsp when "
"defined. The formatter must be able to take the original file as input from "
"stdin and write the formatted file to stdout. The filename of the current "
"buffer can be passed as argument by using the `%{buffer_name}` expansion "
"variable. See below for more information in the [Configuring the formatter "
"command](#configuring-the-formatter-command)"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:70
msgid "`soft-wrap`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:70
msgid "[editor.softwrap](./editor.md#editorsoft-wrap-section)"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:71
msgid "`text-width`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:71
msgid ""
"Maximum line length. Used for the `:reflow` command and soft-wrapping if "
"`soft-wrap.wrap-at-text-width` is set, defaults to `editor.text-width`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:72
msgid "`rulers`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:72
msgid "Overrides the `editor.rulers` config key for the language."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:73
msgid "`path-completion`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:73
msgid "Overrides the `editor.path-completion` config key for the language."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:74
msgid "`workspace-lsp-roots`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:74
msgid ""
"Directories relative to the workspace root that are treated as LSP roots. "
"Should only be set in `.helix/config.toml`. Overwrites the setting of the "
"same name in `config.toml` if set."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:75
msgid "`persistent-diagnostic-sources`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:75
msgid ""
"An array of LSP diagnostic sources assumed unchanged when the language "
"server resends the same set of diagnostics. Helix can track the position for "
"these diagnostics internally instead. Useful for diagnostics that are "
"recomputed on save."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:77
msgid "File-type detection and the `file-types` key"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:79
msgid ""
"Helix determines which language configuration to use based on the `file-"
"types` key from the above section. `file-types` is a list of strings or "
"tables, for example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:83
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"file-types = [\"toml\", { glob = \"Makefile\" }, { glob = \".git/config\" }, "
"{ glob = \".github/workflows/*.yaml\" } ]\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:87
msgid ""
"When determining a language configuration to use, Helix searches the file-"
"types with the following priorities:"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:90
msgid ""
"Glob: values in `glob` tables are checked against the full path of the given "
"file. Globs are standard Unix-style path globs (e.g. the kind you use in "
"Shell) and can be used to match paths for a specific prefix, suffix, "
"directory, etc. In the above example, the `{ glob = \"Makefile\" }` config "
"would match files with the name `Makefile`, the `{ glob = \".git/config\" }` "
"config would match `config` files in `.git` directories, and the `{ glob = "
"\".github/workflows/*.yaml\" }` config would match any `yaml` files in `."
"github/workflow` directories. Note that globs should always use the Unix "
"path separator `/` even on Windows systems; the matcher will automatically "
"take the machine-specific separators into account. If the glob isn't an "
"absolute path or doesn't already start with a glob prefix, `*/` will "
"automatically be added to ensure it matches for any subdirectory."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:101
msgid ""
"Extension: if there are no glob matches, any `file-types` string that "
"matches the file extension of a given file wins. In the example above, the "
"`\"toml\"` config matches files like `Cargo.toml` or `languages.toml`."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:105
msgid "Configuring the formatter command"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:107
msgid ""
"[Command line expansions](./command-line.md#expansions) are supported in the "
"arguments of the formatter command. In particular, the `%{buffer_name}` "
"variable can be passed as argument to the formatter:"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:111
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"formatter = { command = \"mylang-formatter\" , args = [\"--stdin\", \"--"
"stdin-filename %{buffer_name}\"] }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:115
msgid "Language Server configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:117
msgid ""
"Language servers are configured separately in the table `language-server` in "
"the same file as the languages `languages.toml`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:119
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:121
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[language-server.mylang-lsp]\n"
"command = \"mylang-lsp\"\n"
"args = [\"--stdio\"]\n"
"config = { provideFormatter = true }\n"
"environment = { \"ENV1\" = \"value1\", \"ENV2\" = \"value2\" }\n"
"\n"
"[language-server.efm-lsp-prettier]\n"
"command = \"efm-langserver\"\n"
"\n"
"[language-server.efm-lsp-prettier.config]\n"
"documentFormatting = true\n"
"languages = { typescript = [ { formatCommand =\"prettier --stdin-filepath "
"${INPUT}\", formatStdin = true } ] }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

