#: src/languages.md:214
msgid "Tree-sitter grammar configuration"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:216
msgid ""
"The source for a language's tree-sitter grammar is specified in a "
"`[[grammar]]` section in `languages.toml`. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:219
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[[grammar]]\n"
"name = \"mylang\"\n"
"source = { git = \"https://github.com/example/mylang\", rev = "
"\"a250c4582510ff34767ec3b7dcdd3c24e8c8aa68\" }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:225
msgid "Grammar configuration takes these keys:"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:229
msgid "The name of the tree-sitter grammar"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:230
msgid "`source`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:230
msgid ""
"The method of fetching the grammar - a table with a schema defined below"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:232
msgid ""
"Where `source` is a table with either these keys when using a grammar from a "
"git repository:"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:237
msgid "`git`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:237
msgid "A git remote URL from which the grammar should be cloned"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:238
msgid "`rev`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:238
msgid "The revision (commit hash or tag) which should be fetched"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:239
msgid "`subpath`"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:239
msgid ""
"A path within the grammar directory which should be built. Some grammar "
"repositories host multiple grammars (for example `tree-sitter-typescript` "
"and `tree-sitter-ocaml`) in subdirectories. This key is used to point `hx --"
"grammar build` to the correct path for compilation. When omitted, the root "
"of repository is used"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:241
msgid "Choosing grammars"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:243
msgid ""
"You may use a top-level `use-grammars` key to control which grammars are "
"fetched and built when using `hx --grammar fetch` and `hx --grammar build`."
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:246
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"# Note: this key must come **before** the [[language]] and [[grammar]] "
"sections\n"
"use-grammars = { only = [ \"rust\", \"c\", \"cpp\" ] }\n"
"# or\n"
"use-grammars = { except = [ \"yaml\", \"json\" ] }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/languages.md:253
msgid "When omitted, all grammars are fetched and built."
msgstr ""
